\function .decade(n)
[<n>divide[10]floor[]multiply[10]compare:number:gteq[1930]else[pre-1930]addsuffix['s]]
\end

\procedure decade()
<$let year={{{ [<currentTiddler>get[year]] }}}>
<$text text={{{ [.decade<year>] }}}/></$let>
\end

!! Grouped Filter Demo

Demonstrates `group-by` on a `++` filter line.

!!! Group by field

`group-by:period` reads the `period` field on each matched tiddler and produces one collapsible group per distinct value.

<$simple-outline text="""
!! History Notes by Period
  ++ [tag[HistoryOfComputing]sort[title]] group-by:period
""" class="outline" open-depth="1" label-fields="summary caption"/>

---

!!! Group by procedure

`group-by:<<decade>>` invokes a procedure for each tiddler that reads the `year` field and returns a decade string.  The `.decade` helper function does all the work in a single filter pipeline: divide by 10, floor, multiply by 10 to get the decade base, then `compare:number:gteq[1930]else[pre-1930]addsuffix['s]` to produce the label.  Using `sort[year]` in the filter means the groups appear in chronological order.

<$simple-outline text="""
!! History Notes by Decade
  ++ [tag[HistoryOfComputing]sort[year]] group-by:<<decade>>
""" class="outline" open-depth="1" label-fields="summary caption"/>
